  "text": "The addition of inorganic or organic fillers into polymeric materials is an effective way to attain certain desirable properties for different applications [CITATION_1] .The rheological behavior is dependent on the amount of fillers in the liquid polymer. Other factors influencing the viscosity of the highly filled polymers are the particle size and shape, the particle size distribution, the nature of the filler and the polymer matrix, as well as the use of coupling agents or compatibilizers. A detailed description of these influencing factors is given in [CITATION_2] .",
